    {
      "id": "head",
      "english": "head",
      "word": "la cabeza",
      "grammarNote": "Doler (to hurt/ache) works like gustar — the body part is the grammatical subject. 'Me duele la cabeza' = my head hurts (literally: the head pains me). For plural body parts: 'Me duelen los pies' = my feet hurt. The indirect object pronoun (me/te/le) indicates who is hurting.",
      "englishPhrase": "My head hurts.",
      "phrase": "Me duele la cabeza.",
      "literal": "To-me hurts the head."
    },
